Actually, it started out intending to be a straight inversion of the plot of They Live and a couple similar stories  it's just a weird illusion where the lens is reacting anomalously to something completely mundane and harmless. They would still want to contain this thing due to the potential for creating social chaos, but it's not what it seems to be.

Then I thought it would work better if the Foundation isn't sure what's going on:

It's an illusion.

It IS a massive alien conspiracy, but instead of doing the stereotypical  bit, the aliens are REALLY good liars.

There is something anomalous about the people who look  this is just how the SCP-1719 device interprets some other anomaly.

There is an alien conspiracy, but it hasn't played out yet. The aliens are here, but genuinely have no idea what they arethey were left here thousands of years ago and nothing is going to happen until whatever placed them here comes back. If they come back. Maybe they just forgot.

What's really going on? You decide.

So, you see, I don't think I just SCPified They Live, if you consider the story behind the object.








